You want to:

Create a writable sandbox container
Install tools like lynx, wget, etc.
Without needing actual root privileges
Use it for safe browsing/testing inside an isolated environment

to check if thw fakeroot is supported:
singularity build --help | grep fakeroot

singularity build --sandbox output.sif xyz.def 

singularity build --sandbox web_sandbox docker://ubuntu:22.04

singularity shell --writable --fakeroot web_sandbox

apt update && apt install -y wget curl lynx

wget https://example.com
lynx https://example.com


proot=

if not already installed, isntall it via conda: 
conda install -c conda-forge proot


or

curl -LO https://proot.gitlab.io/proot/bin/proot
chmod +x proot
./proot --version



mkdir ubuntu_rootfs
cd ubuntu_rootfs
curl -L https://partner-images.canonical.com/core/focal/current/ubuntu-focal-core-cloudimg-amd64-root.tar.gz | tar xz
cd ..



./proot -R ubuntu_rootfs -0 -b /dev -b /proc -b /sys /bin/bash


apt update
apt install -y wget lynx curl nano


